V1.0.72
     removed heuristic threat assesment option -- too subjective for my liking 
     ca needs to stick to defensible facts.
     alias flag -a now enumerate all aliases
     function flag -f now enumerate all user-functions
     verbose function flag -fv now enumerate ALL functions in the enviroment

V1.0.71
     added support for file hyperlinks for aliases functions and scripts.
     Terminals that support hyperlinks (iTerm2, Kitty, GNOME Terminal) will make it clickable.  on my system they open with gedit
     Other terminals will just display the path normally.

V1.0.70
      new heuristic threat assesment option  flag -t
      scans suid sgid and world writable directories 
      
V1.0.51
     new function to generate hashes of aliases functions binaries and scripts

V1.0.50
     handle more bash operators, pipeline symbols, redirections, etc. during recursion
    
V1.0.48  
     Fixed problem with alias expansion
     code cleanup. -- passed shellcheck

V1.0.45
     did some work on recursive alias expansion - some command operators are now supported
     ui fixes...

V1.0.39
     Fixed problem with variable expansion - Passed Shellcheck

V1.0.38
     Major overhaul of sourced file detection to handle more nested sourced files, conditional sourcing, etc.
     also follows bash internal logic for startup files now.
     detects rhel fedora and adds profile.d/*sh for interactive non login shells

V1.0.32
     support for rpm and packman fixed, nix dropped for now.

V1.0.30
     added experimental support for rpm, pacman and nix file managers

V1.0.28
     fixed a problem with the dependency check

V1.0.27
     limited preview of scripts and functions to 50 lines.
     
V1.0.25
     code cleanup. -- passed shellcheck

V1.0.19
     added support for batcat highlighting with fallback to perl
     fixed $PATH code for (mode : -p)
     code cleanup. ui bug fixes.

V1.0.15
     code cleanup. ui bug fixes.
     added support to display $PATH shadowing for external binaries

V1.0.12 
     code cleanup. ui bug fixes.
     PATH manipulation code consolidated, broken out to a function
     PATH restoration handled by new function and a trap on return

V1.0.7
     Enhanced <TAB> completion, and PATH detection.
     Code cleanup.

V1.0.5 
     Switched to using perl for highlighting instead of sed.  
     Fixed some exe detection code.

